<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,310,908,934]" box="[189,310,908,934]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,908,934]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,908,934]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,956,1163]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Females are similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vachal" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[460,695,956,982]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taeniolellum" subGenus="Hemihalictus">
<emphasis box="[460,484,957,982]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[501,530,957,982]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[548,695,956,982]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">taeniolellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Murao R." box="[871,1038,956,982]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 94" refId="ref41522" refString="Murao R. 2012. Lasioglossum (Evylaeus) tadauchii sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) from Amami- Oshima, southwestern Japan. Esakia 52: 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Murao (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, this species is separated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vachal" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[190,426,992,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taeniolellum" subGenus="Hemihalictus">
<emphasis box="[190,205,993,1018]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">L</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[232,253,993,1018]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[279,426,992,1018]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">taeniolellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the postgena having distinct lineolation over entire surface, the distal process of labrum without lateral projection (
<bibRefCitation author="Murao R." box="[632,778,1029,1055]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 94" refId="ref41522" refString="Murao R. 2012. Lasioglossum (Evylaeus) tadauchii sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) from Amami- Oshima, southwestern Japan. Esakia 52: 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Murao 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5), and T1 with short hairs and fine PP on disc (
<bibRefCitation author="Murao R." box="[197,347,1065,1091]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 94" refId="ref41522" refString="Murao R. 2012. Lasioglossum (Evylaeus) tadauchii sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) from Amami- Oshima, southwestern Japan. Esakia 52: 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Murao 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7). In contrast, in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Vachal" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[613,847,1065,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taeniolellum" subGenus="Hemihalictus">
<emphasis box="[613,629,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">L</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[654,675,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[700,847,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">taeniolellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the lineolation on postgena does not reach the apical margin, the distal process of labrum with horn-like lateral projection (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1211,1101,1127]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="48.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,508,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-151@48.[189,1398,508,1898]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="Fig. 14. Lasioglossum (Hemihalictus) taeniolellum (Vachal, 1903). A. ♀, lateral habitus. B. ♀, head in frontal view. C. ♂, head in frontal view. D. ♀, labrum. E. ♀, mesoscutum. F. ♀, metapostnotum. Scale bars: A = 3 mm; B–C, E–F = 0.5 mm; D = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5235998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5235998/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
), and T1 nearly smooth. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
