<paragraph blockId="47.[189,489,1366,1392]" box="[189,489,1366,1392]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Female: April to October.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,378,1433,1459]" box="[189,378,1433,1459]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,378,1433,1459]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,378,1433,1459]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Flower records</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1096,1480,1507]" box="[189,1096,1480,1507]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Two species in two families were reported as floral records by 
<bibRefCitation author="Murao R." box="[924,1092,1480,1507]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 94" refId="ref41522" refString="Murao R. 2012. Lasioglossum (Evylaeus) tadauchii sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) from Amami- Oshima, southwestern Japan. Esakia 52: 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Murao (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,285,1546,1572]" box="[189,285,1546,1572]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,285,1546,1572]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,285,1546,1572]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[189,1399,1594,1657]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
This species has been collected from around subtropical forests in mountainous area (
<bibRefCitation author="Murao R." box="[1232,1387,1594,1620]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="91 - 94" refId="ref41522" refString="Murao R. 2012. Lasioglossum (Evylaeus) tadauchii sp. nov. (Hymenoptera, Halictidae) from Amami- Oshima, southwestern Japan. Esakia 52: 91 - 94." type="journal article" year="2012">Murao 2012</bibRefCitation>
). It may prefer humid environments.
</paragraph>
